Turkish Yildiz Sells 50% of Coffee Chain to Al Sayer, Vatan Says

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-03-17T08:29:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/turkish-yildiz-sells-50-of-coffee-chain-to-al-sayer-vatan-says.html
Yildiz Holding AS, a Turkish food
company, agreed to sell half of its stake in coffeehouse chain
Cafe Crown to  Kuwait ’s Al Sayer group for $7 million, Vatan
reported, without saying where it got the information.    Yildiz Holding also plans to become a distributor to
Caribou Coffee Co. Inc., the second largest U.S. specialty
coffee chain, in  Turkey ’s $200 million coffee chains market, the
Istanbul-based newspaper said.      Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
